  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This study was designed to investigate the effects of epidural anesthesia combined with
      general anesthesia during laparoscopic surgery. The investigators hypothesized that epidural
      anesthesia will effectively block the activation of the sympathetic nervous system during
      surgery, thus activating nitric oxide and reducing splanchnic ischemia and decrease in
      postoperative renal function.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
